OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1773914711
OL,3,CLong delays as lorry fire closes M5
OL,5,FThe M5 southbound is closed near
OL,6,FStroud after a lorry caught fire.
OL,8,FThe incident happened between junction
OL,9,F13 for Stroud and 14 for Thornbury at
OL,10,Faround 2.25am on Wednesday 18 March.
OL,12,FVehicles have been held since then,
OL,13,Fwith traffic building backing up to
OL,14,FJunction 12 for Quedgeley.
OL,16,FA diversion in place via the A38,
OL,17,Fwhere there are also delays.
OL,19,FPolice and fire crews are at the
OL,20,Fscene, with recovery of the lorry
OL,21,Funlikely until before 6am.
